daily_routine: Every morning at 5:30 AM, Maria checks water temperature readings from
  her underwater sensors. She prepares coral fragment nurseries in the cooler, deeper
  waters, then leads tourists on "ghost reef" tours where she explains what the white
  skeletons used to be. Afternoons spent writing grant applications for restoration
  projects that keep getting defunded as temperatures rise beyond coral survival thresholds.
